{
  "name": "@sargonpiraev/google-calendar-mcp-server",
  "version": "v3",
  "description": "The Google Calendar API is a RESTful API that can be accessed through explicit HTTP calls or using the Google Client Libraries. 
The API exposes most of the features available in the Google Calendar Web interface.

Common terms:
- **Event**: An event on a calendar containing information such as the title, start and end times, and attendees
- **Calendar**: A collection of events with associated metadata such as description or default time zone
- **Calendar List**: A list of all calendars on a user&#x27;s calendar list in the Calendar UI
- **Setting**: A user preference from the Calendar UI, such as the user&#x27;s time zone
- **ACL**: An access control rule granting a user (or group) a specified level of access to a calendar
",
